              },
              "free_text": [
                " ABOUT 1 MICRO-AMP OF PROTONS IN 3 NS BURSTS",
                "        SEPARATED BY 200 NS INCIDENT ON TRITIUM GAS",
                "        TARGET."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".SPECTRA OBTAINED FOR TWO SAMPLES. THE FIRST WEIGHING",
                " 140 GM CONSISTED OF 71.3 PERCENT PB-208, 26.7 PERCENT",
                " PB-206 AND 2.0 PERCENT PB-207. THE SECOND WEIGHING 42",
                " GM CONSISTED OF 88.3 PERCENT PB-206, 8.64 PERCENT PB-",
                " 207 AND 3.04 PERCENT PB-208. TWO SPECTRA SUBTRACTED",
                " TO ELIMINATE PB-206 CONTRIBUTION.",
                ".SAMPLES WERE 2.8 CM DIAMETER CYLINDERS PLACED WITH",
                " THE SYMMETRY AXIS NORMAL TO THE SCATTERING PLANE AT",
                " 0 DEGREES AND 11 CM FROM THE NEUTRON SOURCE."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
